<h1 class="page-title">Admin Panel</h1>

<p class="integration-intro">
  This <strong>admin panel</strong> shows all saved tokens received through webhooks. 
  Please follow the readme to ensure webhooks are configured correctly to receive tokens asynchronously.
</p>

<p class="integration-intro">
  Note that a shopper can have multiple saved tokens per payment method. 
  Select a token to initiate a payment or disable it. 
  Learn more about <a href="https://docs.adyen.com/online-payments/tokenization">tokenization</a>.
</p>

<div class="demo-intro">
  <p>Saved Tokens:</p>
</div>

<div class="token-list">
  {{#if data.length}}
    {{#each data}}
    <div class="token-card">
      <div class="token-header">
        <span class="token-label">Shopper Reference</span>
        <span class="token-value">{{shopperReference}}</span>
      </div>
      <div class="token-details">
        <div class="token-row">
          <span class="token-label">Payment Method</span>
          <span class="token-value">{{paymentMethod}}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="token-row">
          <span class="token-label">Token ID</span>
          <span class="token-value token-id">{{recurringDetailReference}}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="token-actions">
        <a href="/admin/makepayment/{{recurringDetailReference}}" class="button primary">Make Payment</a>
        <a href="/admin/disable/{{recurringDetailReference}}" class="button secondary">Disable Token</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/each}}
  {{else}}
    <div class="empty-state">
      <p>No tokens stored yet.</p>
      <p>Complete a payment in the <a href="/">Shopper View</a> to save a token.</p>
    </div>
  {{/if}}
</div>

<div class="back-link">
  <a href="/" class="back-button">← Back to Shopper View</a>
</div>

